Predicates: Driver(x), Approaching(x,i), Intersection(i), TrafficSignal(i,s), RedLight(s,t), Time(t), Stops(x,i,t), Exempt(x,t). Rule (defeasible deontic form): ∀x ∀i ∀s ∀t. ( Driver(x) ∧ Approaching(x,i) ∧ Intersection(i) ∧ TrafficSignal(i,s) ∧ RedLight(s,t) ∧ ¬Exempt(x,t) ) → OBLIGATORY( Stops(x,i,t) ). Stopping condition: Stops(x,i,t) ≡ ∃t'≤t. Velocity(x,t')=0 ∧ Position(x,t') is at-or-before the stop line of i ∧ ∀t''∈[t',t]. ¬Enters(x,i,t''). Exemptions (non-exhaustive, defeaters): Exempt(x,t) ← EmergencyVehicle(x,t) ∧ SignalsActive(x,t); or ← DirectedByOfficer(x,t) ∧ OfficerOverrides(t); or ← SignalMalfunction(i,t) (treated as all-way stop). Violation predicate: Violates(x,i,t) ← obligation holds ∧ ¬Stops(x,i,t). Sanction rule: Violates(x,i,t) → Liable(x, TrafficOffense, t), with strict liability unless a recognized defense (necessity, duress, mechanical failure) is proven. Notes for downstream reasoning: the rule is a prima facie duty, exemptions act as undercutting defeaters in a defeasible logic (e.g., ASPIC+ or Defeasible Deontic Logic), and the obligation is indexed to time t so compliance is evaluated at the moment the red phase begins, not after entry.
